    <string name="compat_settings_title">Compatibility settings</string>
    <string name="compat_settings_open">Open compatibility settings</string>
    <string name="compat_virtual_fbo_poc_title">Virtual FBO</string>
    <string name="compat_virtual_fbo_poc_desc">Enables GLFrameBuffer Virtual FBO experimental path (amethyst.gdx.virtual_fbo_poc). Used to avoid unknown framebuffer status crashes, but it affects post-processing and can cause some render-skip issues. If you hit rendering-related crashes, consider enabling this option.</string>
    <string name="compat_global_atlas_filter_compat_title">Global atlas filter compatibility patch</string>
    <string name="compat_global_atlas_filter_compat_desc">Newly imported mods are patched offline during import: atlas filter lines containing mipmap are rewritten to Linear,Linear. Keeping this enabled gives higher compatibility; if disabled, new imports will not be patched. Example fix: black blocks on the Ring of Fate main menu.</string>
    <string name="compat_mod_manifest_root_compat_title">ModTheSpire manifest root compatibility patch</string>
    <string name="compat_mod_manifest_root_compat_desc">During mod import, jars are automatically patched when ModTheSpire.json is incorrectly packaged under an outer folder (for example, Fabricate/ModTheSpire.json): it is rewritten to the jar root. Keeping this enabled gives higher compatibility; if disabled, newly imported mods are not patched. A dialog is shown when auto-fix happens.</string>
    <string name="compat_frieren_mod_compat_title">FrierenMod startup compatibility patch</string>
    <string name="compat_frieren_mod_compat_desc">When enabled, importing frierenmod automatically patches FrierenMod/utils/AntiPirateHelper.antiPirate() to remove the desktop anti-piracy dialog path that blocks Android startup at 97%. If disabled, newly imported FrierenMod jars are left untouched.</string>
    <string name="compat_downfall_import_compat_title">Downfall import compatibility patch</string>
    <string name="compat_downfall_import_compat_desc">When enabled, importing downfall automatically patches merchant drawX to use a Settings.WIDTH/xScale-aware position and scales Hexaghost MyBody render offsets with Settings.scale. This targets wide-screen position drift on mobile. If disabled, newly imported Downfall jars are left untouched.</string>
    <string name="compat_vupshion_mod_compat_title">VUPShionMod import compatibility patch</string>
    <string name="compat_vupshion_mod_compat_desc">When enabled, importing vupshionmod automatically patches VUPShionMod/ui/WebButton to remove the Steam workshop subscription gate that can break main-menu background initialization. If disabled, newly imported VUPShionMod jars are left untouched.</string>
    <string name="compat_runtime_texture_compat_title">Runtime texture compatibility patch</string>
    <string name="compat_runtime_texture_compat_desc">Used to fix black blocks caused by dynamically created runtime textures. If you see missing materials/textures, consider enabling it. Pros: continues fixing black blocks not covered during import-time patching. Cons: increases startup CPU/GPU overhead from managed texture scanning, and runtime Linear/Clamp fallback may make some textures blurrier. Default is OFF to prioritize performance.</string>
    <string name="compat_force_linear_mipmap_filter_title">Force linear mipmap filter fallback</string>
    <string name="compat_force_linear_mipmap_filter_desc">When enabled, mipmap-dependent min filters are downgraded to Linear at runtime to avoid black blocks caused by incomplete mip chains in some mods. Example fix: Ring of Fate character models turning into black blocks.</string>
    <string name="compat_non_renderable_fbo_format_compat_title">Non-renderable FBO format fallback</string>
    <string name="compat_non_renderable_fbo_format_compat_desc">When enabled, FrameBuffer formats that cannot be used as color attachments on GLES (Alpha/Intensity/LuminanceAlpha) are automatically upgraded to RGBA8888 to avoid startup crashes such as \"frame buffer could not be constructed: incomplete attachment\". Disabling this is closer to original mod behavior, but may reintroduce startup crashes. If your Haberdashery relic display mod has issues, consider enabling this option.</string>
